13 | title = Ethical and Legal Issues in Neurology Neuroethical issues in clinical neuroscience research | journal = Handbook of Clinical Neurology | volume = 118 | issue = | pages = 335\u2013343 | doi=10.1016/b978-0-444-53501-6.00028-7| pmid = 24182390 | isbn = 9780444535016 }}\n*{{cite journal | author = Fins J.J. | year = 2011 | title = Neuroethics, Neuroimaging, and Disorders of Consciousness: Promise or Peril? | url = | journal = Trans Am Clin Climatol Assoc | volume = 122 | issue = | pages = 336\u2013346 | pmid = 21686236 | pmc = 3116331 }}\n*Daadi, Marcel M; Gary K Steinberg (March 2009). \"Manufacturing neurons from human embryonic stem cells: biological and regulatory aspects to develop a safe cellular product for stroke cell therapy\". Regenerative Medicine 4 (2).\n*{{cite journal |author1=Barker Roger A |author2=de Beaufort Inez | year = 2013 | title = Scientific and ethical issues related to stem cell research and interventions in neurodegenerative disorders of the brain | url = | journal = Progress in Neurobiology | volume = 110 | issue = | pages = 63\u201373 | doi=10.1016/j.pneurobio.2013.04.003|pmid=23665410 }}\n*{{cite journal | author = Hyun Insoo | year = 2010| title = The bioethics of stem cell research and therapy | journal = The Journal of Clinical Investigation | volume = 120 | issue = 1| pages = 71\u201375 | doi=10.1172/jci40435 | pmid=20051638 | pmc=2798696}}\n*{{cite journal|last1=Leefmann|first1=Jon|last2=Levallois|first2=Clement|last3=Hildt|first3=Elisabeth|title=Neuroethics 1995\u20132012. A Bibliometric Analysis of the Guiding Themes of an Emerging Research Field|journal=Frontiers in Human Neuroscience|volume=10|pages=336|year=2016|issn=1662-5161|doi=10.3389/fnhum.2016.00336|pmid=27445772|pmc=4929847}}\n*{{cite journal | author = Gim\u00e9nez-Amaya, Jos\u00e9 Manuel and S\u00e1nchez-Migall\u00f3n, Sergio | year = 2010| title = Anthropological and ethical dilemmas in the recent development of neuroscience | journal = Imago Hominis | volume = 17 | pages = 181\u2013188 }} http://www.imabe.org/index.php?id=1437\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ifi.unizh.ch/~andel/neurowiki/nw.cgi?NeuroPolitics \"NeuroPolitics\"], an entry on ''[[NeuroWiki]]''\n* [https://www.springer.com/12152 Neuroethics] Academic journal, editor: Neil Levy.\n* [http://neuroethics.upenn.edu/ Neuroethics.upenn.edu]\n* [http://repository.upenn.edu/neuroethics_pubs/ Public access journal articles on neuroethics from University of Pennsylvania]\n* [http://ccn.upenn.edu/ The Center for Cognitive Neuroscience, University of Pennsylvania]\n* [http://www.neuroscienceandsociety.org Neuroscience, Identity and Society Seminar Series UK] Further links, research papers and news can be found on the background pages.\n* [http://kolber.typepad.com Neuroethics & Law Blog]\n* [http://brainethics.wordpress.com BrainEthics Blog] This blog is not active any more, but offers a good bibliography up to 2008.\n* [http://neuroethics.upenn.edu/ Center for Neuroscience & Society, University of Pennsylvania]\n* [http://www.ccnelsi.com/ Capital Consortium for Neuroscience: Ethical, Legal and Social Issues] \n* [http://www.nelsi3.com/ Neuroscience: Ethical, Legal and Social Issues - Third Annual Conference] \n* [http://www.ircm.qc.ca/neuroethics/en Neuroethics Research Unit], website of the Neuroethics Research Unit in Montreal, Canada with further links and relevant publications\n* [http://neuroethics.med.ubc.ca/research/ National Core for Neuroethics at the University of British Columbia publications page]\n* [http://www.bioethics.net/journal/ The American Journal of Bioethics]\n* [http://www.asbh.org/ The American Society for Bioethics and Humanities]\n* [http://www.cogneurosociety.org/ Cognitive Neuroscience Society]\n* [http://www.neuroethicssociety.org/ International Neuroethics Society]\n* [http://bioethics.od.nih.gov Bioethics Resources from the NIH]\n* [http://virtualmentor.ama-assn.org/2004/08/rdng1-0408.html Virtual Mentor Ethics Journal of the Ameri